      "message": "I was intrigued, so I tried to repro.\nTurns out you first need to load your CPU a lot:\n$ stress -c \u003cCPU_CORES_COUNT\u003e\nand then inside gerrit package:\n$ go test -race -count 10000 --failfast  \n\nThe failure Internal instead of NotFound isn\u0027t very useful, but TestRestChangeEditFileContent also sometimes fails, I believe for the same reason:\n\n  * /home/tandrii/s/i/infra/go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/common/api/gerrit/rest_test.go \n  Line 380:\n  Expected: nil\n  Actual:   \u0027change edit file content: rpc error: code \u003d Internal desc \u003d failed to execute Post HTTP request: Put \"http://127.0.0.1:36157/changes/someproject~42/edit/some%2Fpath\": net/http: HTTP/1.x transport connection broken: http: CloseIdleConnections called\u0027\n  goroutine 16030 [running]:\n  go.chromium.org/luci/common/api/gerrit.TestRestChangeEditFileContent.func1()\n  \t/home/tandrii/s/i/infra/go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/common/api/gerrit/rest_test.go:380 +0x525\n  \n...\n\n--- FAIL: TestRestChangeEditFileContent (0.03s)\n\n\n\nLooking through golang code, i see the only place where \"CloseIdleConnections called\" is referenced:\nhttps://golang.org/src/net/http/transport.go?s#L736\n\n// CloseIdleConnections closes any connections which were previously\n// connected from previous requests but are now sitting idle in\n// a \"keep-alive\" state. It does not interrupt any connections currently\n// in use.\nfunc (t *Transport) CloseIdleConnections() {\n\t....\n\n\nSo, maybe our new connection is considered not yet \"used\".",
